                .booksRight
                    p.
                        Amazon - Offering glimpses into Lewis's extraordinary relationships and experiences, Jack details
                        the great scholar's life at the Kilns; days at Magdalen College; meetings with the Inklings; marriage
                        to Joy Davidman Gresham; and the creative process that produced such world-famous works as the classic
                        Chronicles of Narnia, Mere Christianity, and The Screwtape Letters.

                    p.
                        This book is an intimate account of the man who helped—and through his works, continues to help—generations
                        hear and understand the heart of Christianity.


