                .booksRight
                    h3 The Screwtape Letters
                    p.
                        In this highly imaginative satire of the human condition, Lewis uses a correspondence
                        between the demon Screwtape and his nephew to speak to the human failings and
                        temptations common to all. By the medium and unveiling truth of his observations
                        he manages the rare pairing of both humour and seriousness. Read for laughs
                        and reproof, enjoyment and instruction.

            hr

